Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need
to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with
@oil{} and season with a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat in the oil,
then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).
Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.
Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).
Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Chop the
@paneer{250%g} into 2cm wide cubes. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can}
using a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot,
add the paneer. Fry the paneer, turning regularly, until golden all over,
~{4-5%minutes}, then pop into a #bowl{}. Sprinkle over a @salt{pinch} and set to one
side. Keep the pan!

Return the now empty frying pan to a medium-high heat. Add another splash of
@oil{}. Once hot, add the onion and pepper to the pan and cook until softened,
~{4-5%minutes}. Once soft, stir in the garlic and @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1%tsp}
(careful, it's hot!). Cook for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the black beans and the
@water{100%ml}. Lightly crush half of the beans with the back of a #fork{}.

Add the paneer back into the pan and gently stir in the @mango chutney{80%g} until
melted. Mix in half the coriander and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Remove from the heat.

When the wedges have 5 mins left in the oven, pop the @garlic and coriander naan{4}
onto the middle shelf of the oven to warm though, ~{5-6%minutes}. Remove them from
the oven and once cool enough to handle, slice an opening on one side of the naan
to make a pocket. Spoon the filling into the naan pockets. Divide the filled naan
pockets and wedges between your plates, sprinkle over the remaining coriander and
serve with @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g}. Enjoy!